title: TidGi Feature Handbook/TidGi Mini Window
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The TidGi Mini Window is a floating window you can summon at any time with a global keyboard shortcut, letting you quickly jot down or look up notes without switching apps.

!! Enabling the Mini Window

# Open TidGi settings (gear icon at the bottom of the sidebar)
# Find the "TidGi Mini Window" section
# Toggle it on; a TidGi icon appears in the system tray and the mini window is created (hidden by default)

!! Setting a Global Shortcut

# On the "TidGi Mini Window" settings page, click the "Register Shortcut" button
# Press the key combination you want (e.g. `Ctrl+Shift+M` / `Command+Shift+M`)
# Click "Confirm" to save

After that, pressing the shortcut from any application shows the mini window; pressing it again hides it.

!! Mini Window Options

* ''Always on Top'': when enabled, the mini window floats above all other windows
* ''Sync Workspace with Main Window'': when enabled, switching workspaces in the main window also switches the mini window to the same workspace

!! Notes

* The mini window displays the full TiddlyWiki interface — you can read and edit normally
* Disabling the mini window toggle destroys the floating window
